The paper deals with computational social choice problems, which are typically studied in the subfield of computer science called "computational game theory" (cs.GT). The paper also proposes new algorithms for solving these problems, which falls under the subfield of "artificial intelligence" (cs.AI). The algorithms are based on the structure of the preferences, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of "data structures and algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper also involves analyzing the relationships among different types of preferences, which could be relevant to the subfield of "machine learning" (cs.LG) or "social and information networks" (cs.SI).
